3. cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) - The paper's main focus is on social networks and their characteristics, making this category a likely fit. 
4. cs.CY (Cryptography and Security) - The paper may also be relevant to cryptography and security as it discusses the analysis of online social networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper may also be relevant to data structures and algorithms as it discusses the computation of metrics in social networks.
